text: Hunt County is a county in the U.S. state of Texas. In 2020, 99,956 people lived there. The county seat is Greenville. == History == Hunt County was made in 1846. == Geography == Hunt County has a total area of 882 square miles. == Places == === Cities === * Greenville (county seat) === Towns === * Neylandville == References == Category:Texas counties
title: Hunt County, Texas
